*Competing “classical” models of allostery*

1. Sequential model: focuses on tertiary changes at one active site induced by the binding of a ligand at another binding site (KNF model) – induced fit

#image("/assets/Screenshot 2025-12-14 at 11.30.56 PM.png")
2. MWC (Monod-Wyman-Changeux model): focuses on concerted change in quaternary structure. well in quant. system，e.g. hemoglobin.
  - assumes allosteric proteins are oligomers of identical subunits
  - assumes all sites must be either high affinity or low affinity: symmetry
  - assumes change in shape of the entire molecule R (relaxed) and T (tense) states

MWC Model for Cooperativity: Three independent adjustable parameters
$K_R$ and $K_T$: association constants, $L$: equilibrium constant



