Proteins are dynamic:
1. many vibrational movements
2. these movements are represented by the many possible protein states

Ligand binding can 
- shift the equilibrium to favor one of these states, similar to the idea of an equilibrium between the R and T states
- either decrease or increase the configurational entropy of the protein
